{"title": "Concealing Canvas", "content": "Somebody's hidden a safe, or other valuable object, behind a painting on the wall. In a common joke, the safe is hidden behind a painting of a safe.\n\nTo be fair, a painting is probably the easiest object to hide a safe behind; on the other hand, behind a painting is consequently the most obvious place to look for a safe. People rarely seem to consider installing safes behind other common objects hanging on walls, such as mirrors or tapestries.\n\nSometimes the painting will suggest the presence of the safe, the nature of the valuables or perhaps even be a clue to the safe's code.\n\nThis is ridiculously common in Interactive Fiction and Point And Click Games.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ConcealingCanvas", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/KathyRain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheFlyingCloud", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Hoodwinked", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/WallaceAndGromit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheWrongTrousers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BackToTheFuturePartII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Thunderball", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Valkyrie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/KindHeartsAndCoronets", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SherlockHolmes2009", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/ThePinkPanther", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/Sleuth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCobbler", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HudsonHawk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheClimax", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ArtemisFowl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/FrederickForsyth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheFourthProtocol", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheThreeInvestigators", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DCComics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Knightfall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheExecutioner", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheFlyingCloud", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Heroes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheMonkees", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Lost", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Leverage", "/pmwi